    "answer": "The Status Network is actively developing a zero-gas transaction system that leverages cryptographic techniques such as RLN (Rate Limiting Nullifier) to enable gasless transactions at scale ([Status Network Documentation](https://docs.status.network/general-info/gasless-transactions)). RLN uses zero-knowledge proofs to verify group membership without revealing identities, allowing users to transact without paying gas fees unless they exceed their transaction limits, which then exposes them to penalties ([Status Network Documentation](https://docs.status.network/general-info/gasless-transactions)). This system supports large-scale membership proofs via Sparse Merkle Trees, accommodating up to a million accounts efficiently.\n\nFor proof anchoring and verifiable agent task completion, the Status Network ecosystem supports deploying and verifying smart contracts on its Sepolia testnet, accessible via tools like Remix, Hardhat, and the Status Bridge for token transfers between Sepolia (Layer 1) and Status Network (Layer 2) ([Status Network Quick Start](https://docs.status.network/introduction/quick-start), [Bridge Documentation](https://docs.status.network/tools/bridge)). The Status Network also provides a block explorer for monitoring transactions and verifying smart contracts ([Status Network Block Explorer](https://docs.status.network/tools/block-explorers)). Additionally, recent innovations include the development of AI on-chain agents, which can interact with blockchain protocols, execute transactions, and support verifiable identities using standards like ERC-8004, facilitating autonomous and verifiable agent workflows ([sebasneuron/onchain-agent-kit](https://github.com/sebasneuron/onchain-agent-kit)).\n\nFurthermore, the network's economic model emphasizes yield-backed funding and native app fees to support its gasless infrastructure, with ongoing efforts to anchor verifiable human-AI distinctions through zero-knowledge proofs, such as Groth16, for enhanced privacy and verification ([Status Network Blog](https://status.network/blog/status-network-economic-model-yield-funding-pool-and-zero-gas), [Medium article](https://medium.com/@lhmisme2011/project-vata-building-verifiable-human-ai-distinction-with-groth16-zero-knowledge-proofs-and-b87d182e5591)).",
